parts: How many independent candidates are there in Singapore's General Election 2025?

content.text: search("How many independent candidates are there in Singapore's General Election 2025?")

parts:
As of Nomination Day on April 23, 2025, two independent candidates are contesting in Singapore's General Election 2025:

1. **Jeremy Tan** is running in Mountbatten Single Member Constituency (SMC). He announced his candidacy out of a sense of civic duty. citeturn0search2

2. **Darryl Lo Kar Keong**, a 28-year-old law graduate from Singapore Management University, is contesting in Radin Mas SMC. He expressed concerns about the lack of credible opposition in his constituency. citeturn0search12

These two independents are part of a record-breaking total of 211 candidates contesting in GE2025, surpassing the previous high of 210 candidates in post-independence Singapore. citeturn0search0
